Characteristics[Organism]: young seedlings of Nipponbare (Oryza sativa, ssp. japonica)
Comment[Instrument]: LC-MS/MS analyses were performed on an Easy-nLC 1000 liquid chromatography system (Thermo, Waltham, WA, USA) coupled to a Q-Exactive Plus via a nano-electrospray ion source (Thermo).
Comment[FragmentationMethod]: fragmentation in the HCD cell at normalized collision energy of 27%
Comment[EnrichmentMethod]: peptides were incubated with TiO2 beads (GL sciences, Tokyo, Japan)
Comment[MS2MassAnalyzer]: Orbitrap analyzer operating at a resolution of 17,500 at m/z 400
Comment[Separation]: separated on a homemade 100 µm ID × 10 cm column (C18, 1.9 µm, 120 Å, Maisch GmbH)
Comment[NumberOfMissedCleavages]: Two missed cleavage on trypsin was allowed.
